HEADWORD: Organist
<hw>Or"gan*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>organiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>One who
plays on the organ.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>One of the priests who
organized or sung in parts.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Organista</ent>⟦br⟧
